SNICKERDOODLES
3 3/4 c all-purpose flour		2 c + 3 Tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp baking soda			2 eggs
1/2 tsp cream of tartar			1/4 c milk
1/2 tsp salt				1 tsp vanilla
1 c butter or margarine			1 tsp cinnamon

Stir together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt.  Beat
butter for 30 seconds.  Add 2 c sugar and beat until fluffy.  add
eggs, milk, and vanilla, beating well.  Add dry ingredients to beaten
mixture, blending thoroughly.  Form dough into 1-inch balls (it may
help to refrigerate the dough for an hour first).  Mix remaining sugar
with cinnamon, and roll dough balls in this mixture.  Place balls on
cookie sheet and flatten slightly with the bottom of a drinking glass.
Bake at 375 for 8 minutes or until lightly golden.
